[Just because an animal has neurological signs, one should not automatically conclude that rabies is the cause. Rather, an examination by a veterinarian and a thorough history should be taken. The differential list for diseases producing neurological diseases in horses can be long, as this article listed several. Rabies should always be on the differential list when dealing with any animal with neurological signs. - Mod.TG

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3924945,6.]
